Trigger warning: This isn’t a funny post and I know that but, the majority of “funny” people are in a great deal of pain or have been at one or many points in their life. I’m sharing this little piece of my story as a warning to those of you who trust anyone with your children— including your new partners. While it’s never anyone’s fault but the perpetrator, here are a few warning signs for sexual abuse of young children, because the fact remains that every nine minutes a new child sexual abuse report is placed: 

1. Excessive talk about or knowledge of sexual topics
2. Keeping secrets, or not talking as much as usual
3. Not wanting to be left alone with certain people or being afraid to be away from primary caregivers, especially if this is a new behavior
4. Regressive behaviors or resuming behaviors they had grown out of, such as thumbsucking, playing with feces, or bedwetting
5. Overly compliant behavior
6. Sexual behavior that is inappropriate for the child’s age
7. Spending an unusual amount of time alone
8. Trying to avoid removing clothing to change or bathe
10. Change in eating habits
11. Change in mood or personality, such as increased aggression
12. Decrease in confidence or self-image
13. Excessive worry or fearfulness
14. Increase in unexplained health problems such as stomach 15. aches and headaches
16. Loss or decrease in interest in school, activities, and friends
17. Nightmares or fear of being alone at night
18. Self-harming behaviors

If you would like to learn more or report an instance of abuse, please call the National Sexual Assault Hotline at 800.656.HOPE (4673) or chat online at online.rainn.org. #survivor

I will never forget people making fun of my belly button size post tumor + endo removal surgery. A belly button, bro. I saw so many comments like this and ignored them because people really don’t know any better. 

Body shaming is so common now that everyone feels like they have to be “perfect”. You don’t. But it feels like it. 

End of the day, they had to pull my guts through my belly button during laparoscopic surgery to save my life… but that doesn’t matter, because people be peopling. 😭

Over time, it shrunk down to its original size. Some things won’t or can’t be changed though. And a lot of y’all (not all) be bullying people for existing & I don’t like that. 

Can we all just be kind to each other? Why comment on each others bodies and clothes or bad dancing skills at the bar when we could just,I don’t know, focus on living this one life we have as freely and happily as humanly possible? And support others in doing the same? Hm? It would be so nice. 😭

I can’t WAIT until it’s mainstream to consider people who put others down LAME. Because it is. It’s SO lame! People gossiping and shaming others should get BOMBASTIC side eyes!!! I’m not laughing with you OR at all! It’s not funny! It’s mean & shows how insecure you feel in your own skin. I’m inspired by those who live their lives fully & without consideration for other peoples judgments! Keep living!

Yooooo!!! I went through so much last year! I got diagnosed with multiple tumors & cysts, two serious autoimmune diseases, went through my first serious break up, lost several family members, couldn’t eat food, lost an extreme amount of weight from illness, lost friends, got three major surgeries (at once!) with no family in LA, suffered through depression, suicidal ideation, and struggled to work through it all just to keep a roof over my head. And did it sick! Did it suffering! Did it scared, bruh! Shot my first ever feature film!!

So many people distanced themselves because they simply didn’t know what to say, or what to do, or didn’t understand what I was going through. I literally had someone drop me as a friend for missing their bday party because I was sick & suffering! Others didn’t want to say the wrong thing, so they just didn’t say anything at all. I get it. 

I realized a couple of my friends were fake, surface level, or using me for this or that, because when I got sick and had to start saying “no” to editing, writing, filming… they got angry. I realized they were just unsafe spaces born out of a time in my life when I was troubled, desperate for connection & to be loved because I didn’t truly love myself! I didn’t even recognize I could be used for something because I didn’t know what I had that someone else would possibly want from me. I was broken & blind to my worth. 

I’ve learned so much, grown so much. And this woman right here?! This woman right hereeee, nigga?! I LOVE HER! I’M PROUD OF HER! I’M GRATEFUL TO BE HERE! I EARNED THIS SHIT. AND WHEN I DROP ALLLLLL THESE RANDOM ASS BLESSINGS ON Y’ALL THIS YEAR, KNOW GOD & I FOUGHT FOR EM! I didn’t think I deserved to be here. I didn’t think I had a purpose! But God knew my purpose. He held me through it. And my dog. And some good people. And food. Omgggg. Food was in my corner, man lol

I say all this to say, if you’re broken… don’t be afraid to piece yourself back together. Yeah, you won’t be the same. But you’ll be better for it. It’s the process of rebuilding in and of itself that makes you stronger. Pick up the pieces. Forgive what broke you. And move into the new beginning of your story ❤️🥰

I want to send my immense love to @sacredsisters for curating an enchanting full day gala, where we healed our hearts through art therapy with @adriane.leigh, profound somatic healing techniques led by @reta.grace, empowering breath work by Bianca Harris, and a celestial sound bath by @curl.crush.yoga. 🫶🏽

As the day faded, we gathered around a table adorned with love (thank you to @soundofflow & partner) that marked not just a year of sisterhood, but also the profound strides we've taken in our healing journeys.

These past years have taken me through a landscape of growth, revealing my contributions to both challenges and triumphs. 

Today, I find myself center stage in an abundant garden of healing, watching my own evolution unfold in real-time. This path, albeit rocky at times, led me to this sisterhood… a tapestry of incredible women who have become part of my chosen family. 🥹

My life has been one of unearthing strength + grace as I navigate the path to heal from CPTSD. It hasn’t been easy but with care, I've nurtured a relationship with my inner child, allowing wounds to mend and scars to gently fade. 

Sacred Sister’s has taught me to cradle my history with kindness, weaving resilience and self-love into my narrative. I'm in awe of this journey, embracing where I stand, and the beautiful souls that now fill my life.

I will always remember the grounding cacao ceremony by @cosmicallyshonna and the sweat-inducing yoga that added so much playfulness to our day by @aceyogala. 😂 

These experiences are etched into my heart, reminding me of the depth and authenticity we all share.

I’m embracing the winding path of healing, the connections of sisterhood that run so, so deep, and the gift of being wholly present in all the lavish moments. 😉

Remember, every woman you encounter is you— compliment her, affirm her, treat her with the care and understanding that you seek for yourself. We all need each other more than we know and I’ll carry everything I’ve learned from this collective into every place I go. 💫🥹 @laurahuertasphoto & @lilianelathan #sacredsisters #healingjourney #sisterhood #innerchildhealing
